---
import BaseLayout from '@/components/layout/BaseLayout.astro';
---

<BaseLayout
  title="About — Moe Qadan"
  description="UX engineer and platform systems owner at MagTek. Working at the intersection of design, front-end engineering, and AI-native workflows."
>
  <div class="about-page">
    <div class="about-hero">
      <div class="container-site">
        <span class="badge badge-muted animate-fade-up">About</span>
        <h1 class="about-title animate-fade-up animate-delay-100">
          I work on platforms.<br />
          <em>Not just pages.</em>
        </h1>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="container-site about-body">
      <div class="about-grid">
        <!-- Main narrative -->
        <div class="about-narrative">
          <p class="about-lead">
            I'm Moe Qadan — a UX engineer and front-end systems owner who works
            at the intersection of design, implementation, and platform architecture.
          </p>

          <p class="about-para">
            My day-to-day involves owning and evolving the UX across approximately
            85% of MagTek's primary production website, plus maintaining front-end
            consistency and system integrity across 11 additional properties that
            share the same architecture. This is platform-level work, not feature work.
          </p>

          <p class="about-para">
            The stack is real: ASP.NET MVC 5, Razor views, Bootstrap, jQuery, Entity
            Framework, Web API 2, IIS. A long-lived monolith with real constraints,
            real production traffic, and real consequences when something breaks. I don't
            avoid this kind of environment — I've learned to work inside it effectively,
            which is a different and harder skill than building on a clean stack.
          </p>

          <p class="about-para">
            Hardware interface design at MagTek also taught me that constraints are
            specific: glare-heavy environments, operator gloves, PCI compliance,
            embedded terminal displays. Generic UI patterns don't survive contact with
            these realities. You think from first principles or you build something
            that looks fine in Figma and fails in the field.
          </p>

          <p class="about-para">
            Over the past year, I've been integrating AI — specifically Claude and Cursor
            — as structural participants in my workflow. Not as autocomplete. As a designed
            process where structured specs become the input, agents handle the implementation
            layer, and I own the review, direction, and quality standard. The distinction
            matters: improvised AI use produces inconsistent results; designed AI workflows
            produce consistent ones.
          </p>

          <blockquote class="about-quote">
            "The most interesting work happens inside real systems with real constraints —
            not in greenfield projects with perfect stacks."
          </blockquote>

          <p class="about-para">
            I'm interested in problems that require both design judgment and implementation
            depth — places where you can't separate "what it should be" from "what it can
            be built to be." That's where the combination of disciplines matters most.
          </p>
        </div>

        <!-- Sidebar -->
        <div class="about-sidebar">
          <div class="about-card">
            <h2 class="about-card-title">Profile</h2>
            <div class="about-fact-list">
              <div class="about-fact">
                <span class="fact-label">Primary role</span>
                <span class="fact-value">UX Engineer / Platform Systems</span>
              </div>
              <div class="about-fact">
                <span class="fact-label">Platform</span>
                <span class="fact-value">MagTek.com + 11 additional sites</span>
              </div>
              <div class="about-fact">
                <span class="fact-label">Stack (production)</span>
                <span class="fact-value">ASP.NET MVC, Razor, Bootstrap, jQuery, Entity Framework</span>
              </div>
              <div class="about-fact">
                <span class="fact-label">Stack (modern)</span>
                <span class="fact-value">Astro, TypeScript, React, Tailwind</span>
              </div>
              <div class="about-fact">
                <span class="fact-label">AI workflow</span>
                <span class="fact-value">Claude + Cursor, structured production pipeline</span>
              </div>
              <div class="about-fact">
                <span class="fact-label">Location</span>
                <span class="fact-value">United States · Remote-capable</span>
              </div>
            </div>
          </div>

          <div class="about-card">
            <h2 class="about-card-title">What I do well</h2>
            <ul class="about-role-list">
              <li>Platform-level UX systems ownership</li>
              <li>Front-end architecture in legacy environments</li>
              <li>Design-to-implementation without translation loss</li>
              <li>Structured AI workflow design</li>
              <li>Hardware interface UX</li>
              <li>Multi-site consistency at scale</li>
            </ul>
          </div>

          <div class="about-card about-card--contact">
            <h2 class="about-card-title">Get in touch</h2>
            <p class="about-card-note">
              If you're working on something interesting — complex systems,
              platform engineering, AI-native product work — I'm always open
              to a conversation.
            </p>
            <div class="about-links">
              <a href="mailto:muhammedqadan@outlook.com" class="about-link-btn about-link-btn--primary">
                <svg width="14" height="14" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" aria-hidden="true">
                  <path d="M4 4h16c1.1 0 2 .9 2 2v12c0 1.1-.9 2-2 2H4c-1.1 0-2-.9-2-2V6c0-1.1.9-2 2-2z"/>
                  <polyline points="22,6 12,13 2,6"/>
                </svg>
                Email
              </a>
              <a href="https://linkedin.com/in/muhammedqadan" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer" class="about-link-btn">
                LinkedIn
              </a>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <!-- How I work section -->
      <div class="about-principles">
        <h2 class="principles-title">How I work</h2>
        <div class="principles-grid">
          <div class="principle">
            <div class="principle-num">01</div>
            <h3 class="principle-name">Systems before solutions</h3>
            <p class="principle-desc">
              Every problem is more interesting at the system level. I'd rather
              understand the structure that produces an issue than patch the symptom.
              This takes longer upfront and compounds in your favor over time.
            </p>
          </div>
          <div class="principle">
            <div class="principle-num">02</div>
            <h3 class="principle-name">Constraints are information</h3>
            <p class="principle-desc">
              A legacy monolith, a PCI compliance requirement, a 10-year-old jQuery
              dependency — these aren't obstacles to work around. They're the actual
              design brief. The best work accounts for them, not around them.
            </p>
          </div>
          <div class="principle">
            <div class="principle-num">03</div>
            <h3 class="principle-name">Designed AI, not improvised AI</h3>
            <p class="principle-desc">
              I build workflows where AI operates inside a structure I've designed —
              explicit inputs, explicit outputs, human judgment at every checkpoint.
              The difference between this and ad-hoc prompting is the same difference
              between a system and a habit.
            </p>
          </div>
          <div class="principle">
            <div class="principle-num">04</div>
            <h3 class="principle-name">Implement what you design</h3>
            <p class="principle-desc">
              The gap between design intent and built output is where quality disappears.
              Working across both sides closes the gap by construction rather than
              by coordination. I don't hand things off to myself — I finish them.
            </p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</BaseLayout>

<style>
  .about-hero {
    padding-top: calc(64px + var(--space-16));
    padding-bottom: var(--space-12);
    border-bottom: 1px solid var(--color-border);
    margin-bottom: var(--space-12);
  }

  .about-title {
    font-family: var(--font-display);
    font-size: clamp(44px, 6vw, 80px);
    font-weight: 400;
    letter-spacing: -0.03em;
    line-height: 1.05;
    color: var(--color-text);
    margin-top: var(--space-4);
  }

  .about-title em {
    font-style: italic;
    color: var(--color-accent);
  }

  .about-body {
    padding-bottom: var(--space-24);
  }

  .about-grid {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: 1fr;
    gap: var(--space-10);
    margin-bottom: var(--space-16);
  }

  @media (min-width: 1024px) {
    .about-grid {
      grid-template-columns: 1fr 320px;
      gap: var(--space-16);
    }
  }

  .about-lead {
    font-size: clamp(18px, 2.5vw, 21px);
    font-weight: 500;
    color: var(--color-text);
    line-height: 1.6;
    margin-bottom: var(--space-6);
  }

  .about-para {
    font-size: 17px;
    color: var(--color-text-muted);
    line-height: 1.75;
    margin-bottom: var(--space-5);
    max-width: 62ch;
  }

  .about-quote {
    border-left: 3px solid var(--color-accent);
    padding: var(--space-4) var(--space-6);
    margin: var(--space-8) 0;
    background-color: var(--color-accent-dim);
    border-radius: 0 var(--radius-md) var(--radius-md) 0;
    font-size: 17px;
    color: var(--color-text);
    font-style: italic;
    font-family: var(--font-display);
    line-height: 1.6;
  }

  .about-sidebar {
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    gap: var(--space-4);
  }

  .about-card {
    padding: var(--space-5);
    border-radius: var(--radius-xl);
    border: 1px solid var(--color-border);
    background-color: var(--color-bg-elevated);
  }

  .about-card--contact {
    border-color: var(--color-accent-muted);
    background-color: var(--color-accent-dim);
  }

  .about-card-title {
    font-size: 11px;
    font-weight: 700;
    letter-spacing: 0.06em;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    color: var(--color-text-subtle);
    margin-bottom: var(--space-4);
  }

  .about-fact-list {
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    gap: var(--space-4);
  }

  .about-fact {
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    gap: 3px;
  }

  .fact-label {
    font-size: 11px;
    font-weight: 600;
    letter-spacing: 0.04em;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    color: var(--color-text-subtle);
  }

  .fact-value {
    font-size: 13px;
    color: var(--color-text);
    font-weight: 500;
    line-height: 1.4;
  }

  .about-role-list {
    list-style: none;
    padding: 0;
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    gap: var(--space-2);
  }

  .about-role-list li {
    font-size: 13px;
    color: var(--color-text);
    font-weight: 500;
    padding: var(--space-2) 0;
    border-bottom: 1px solid var(--color-border-subtle);
    line-height: 1.4;
  }

  .about-role-list li:last-child { border-bottom: none; }

  .about-role-list li::before {
    content: '→ ';
    color: var(--color-accent);
    font-weight: 700;
  }

  .about-card-note {
    font-size: 13px;
    color: var(--color-text-muted);
    line-height: 1.6;
    margin-bottom: var(--space-4);
  }

  .about-links {
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    gap: var(--space-2);
  }

  .about-link-btn {
    display: inline-flex;
    align-items: center;
    gap: 8px;
    padding: 10px 16px;
    border-radius: var(--radius-md);
    font-size: 14px;
    font-weight: 500;
    text-decoration: none;
    border: 1px solid var(--color-border);
    color: var(--color-text-muted);
    background-color: var(--color-bg);
    transition: all 150ms;
  }

  .about-link-btn:hover {
    color: var(--color-text);
    border-color: var(--color-accent);
    background-color: var(--color-accent-dim);
  }

  .about-link-btn--primary {
    background-color: var(--color-accent);
    color: var(--color-bg);
    border-color: var(--color-accent);
    font-weight: 600;
  }

  .about-link-btn--primary:hover {
    background-color: var(--color-accent-hover);
    color: var(--color-bg);
    border-color: var(--color-accent-hover);
  }

  .about-principles {
    padding-top: var(--space-12);
    border-top: 1px solid var(--color-border);
  }

  .principles-title {
    font-size: 28px;
    font-weight: 700;
    letter-spacing: -0.02em;
    color: var(--color-text);
    margin-bottom: var(--space-8);
  }

  .principles-grid {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: 1fr;
    gap: var(--space-4);
  }

  @media (min-width: 640px) {
    .principles-grid { grid-template-columns: repeat(2, 1fr); }
  }

  .principle {
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    gap: var(--space-3);
    padding: var(--space-5);
    border-radius: var(--radius-lg);
    border: 1px solid var(--color-border);
    background-color: var(--color-bg-elevated);
  }

  .principle-num {
    font-size: 11px;
    font-weight: 700;
    letter-spacing: 0.08em;
    color: var(--color-accent);
    font-family: var(--font-mono);
  }

  .principle-name {
    font-size: 15px;
    font-weight: 700;
    letter-spacing: -0.01em;
    color: var(--color-text);
    line-height: 1.3;
  }

  .principle-desc {
    font-size: 13px;
    color: var(--color-text-muted);
    line-height: 1.65;
  }
</style>
